Saratchand Tadepalli, eLearning services, Sify Technologies Limited, India Soft-2012 





Saratchand Tadepalli, eLearning services, Sify Technologies Limited, India Soft-2012 





 Executives




          Raju Vegesna ,
          Chairman & Managing Director 
Raju Vegesna is an Executive and Entrepreneur who has leveraged his technology vision and leadership skills into a multi-decade series of successes in high technology industries. Most recently, Raju was the Founder and CEO of ServerEngines, an industry leader in network and storage convergence products that grew rapidly from its inception in 2003, with significant operations in California, Texas and India.

ServerEngines was acquired in August, 2010, by Emulex, and Raju joined Emulex as Chief Strategist, responsible for the company's strategic direction and evangelizing the adoption of Emulex products to key customers and partners.    Mr. Vegesna currently serves as the Chairman and Managing Director of Sify Technologies Limited, a publicly traded ICT services company based in India after having purchased a majority stake in 2005. Realizing the emerging potential for Enterprise IT business both within and outside India, Mr. Vegesna set about aligning the company’s focus towards the same. Less than half a decade later, Sify is now recognized as a leader in the fast growing segments of ICT services, managed IT services, Connectivity, Voice and Cloud services. 

In recognition of his entrepreneurial achievements, Raju was honored at the India Splendor Award event at UCLA in 2007.      Raju has proven to be a gifted entrepreneur, having founded multiple highly-successful startup companies. In 1994, prior to his current involvement with ServerEngines and Sify, Raju founded ServerWorks Corporation and, as Chairman and CEO, led ServerWorks to become the world leader in computer chipsets, commanding a 90% market share in the x86 server chipset market.

        

          Kamal Nath,
          Chief Executive Officer
Kamal Nath joined Sify to drive Sify 3.0, the vision to make Sify Technologies a Services and Solutions leader.   He moves here after a stellar innings with IT major, HCL Tech. In his 17 years long tenure at HCL Tech, he has led various transformational engagements with large enterprises, incubated business lines, created innovative business models and opened up new and high growth verticals for HCL Tech.

Kamal was a Founder Member of HCL Comnet, the Infrastructure Services division of HCL Tech and has been a key member of HCL Tech’s growth story over the years.          His entrepreneurial style of functioning along with strategic vision, innovation and leadership skills has seen him play several roles across different business units of HCL. In a career spanning 22 years, he has accumulated in-depth knowledge of Systems Integration Services, IT Infrastructure Management Services, Technology Integration Services & Strategic Outsourcing.  His experience and engagement with customers of various verticals encompassing BFSI, Public Services, Energy & Utilities, Large Business Conglomerates, Manufacturing, Retail and others will be a key asset at Sify.    Kamal holds a degree in Electronics and Communications from BIT, Sindri.

        

           m.p. Vijay Kumar ,
          Chief Financial Officer 
Vijay Kumar, a rank holder in Chartered Accountancy, is a Cost Accountant and Company Secretary.   He joined Sify in 2007 as the CFO and has been a key member of Sify’s transformation into a leading Enterprise IT Infra and Services player.    Director on the Board of Sify Software Limited, Sify Technologies Singapore Pte Limited, National Internet Exchange of India (Nixi) and Thejo Engineering Limited-the first company to be listed in SME Platform “Emerge” of National Stock Exchange (NSE). He was earlier on the Board of MFG Sify Securities Limited.   He was a partner for over 7 years with Yoganandh & Ram, an established firm of Chartered Accountants, Chennai and registered with PCAOB, US.   Prior to joining Yoganandh & Ram, he was employed with Sundaram Finance Services Ltd. (SFSL), Chennai, the Investment Banking arm of Sundaram Finance Limited, a top-notch NBFC that provides a wide range of financial services. His responsibilities during his 7 year stint included Head - Investment Banking, Head - Finance, Accounts and Company Secretary. He was Assistant General Manager (IB) & Secretary when the entrepreneurship bug bit and he decided to move to Yoganandh & Ram.   He is a Member of the Accounting Standards Board of ICAI, Accounting Standards Board of CII, Task Force on Accounting for Rate Regulated entities Editorial Board of SIRC of ICAI, Corporate Laws committee of ICAI and also member of several study groups of ICAI on Accounting Standards, Audit Assurance Standards and Company Law.  He is a prominent speaker on the professional circuit in India, the Middle East and South East Asia on International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS), Indian Accounting Standards, Management Audit, Corporate Laws and Capital Market.   A well referenced resource person on Accountancy, Corporate Laws and Capital market, he is associated with the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India, the Institute of Company Secretaries of India and Bharatidasan Institute of Management (BIM). Also a successful author, he has over 8 popular titles on Accounting, Accounting Standards, Audit Standards and Company Law that have since enjoyed continious reprints.      A Member of Institute of Internal Auditors (IIA), Florida, USA, he is presently the Governor and Vice President on the Board of Governors, Chennai Chapter of IIA and was Chairman of Heads of Finance Forum for FY 11-12 and 12-13, CII, Tamil Nadu. This year, he joins the Southern Regional Council as a Special Invitee mandated with providing thought leadership and strategic direction for the year 2013-14.   He is active in corporate relations, serving Rotary in various capacities as a Rotary Paul Harris Fellow. 

        

          David Nishball ,
          Chief Strategy Officer
David Nishball is one of the leading experts in building and managing Enterprise telecom operations in the Asia Pacific Region, having led the Enterprise segment for a number of global operators, joint venture companies, and emerging market operators.      He brings over twenty eight years of experience spanning various roles and functions in the telecommunications industry, including 18 years in the Asia Pacific Region. Most recently, David was President of Airtel Enterprise Services from 2007-2010. Enterprise Services is a strategic business unit of Bharti Airtel Ltd., India's leading telecom service provider.   Prior to joining Bharti Airtel, David was a Senior Vice President, Asia Pacific, for Orange Business Services (formerly Equant), based in Singapore. He managed Orange's business operations in ASEAN, Japan, Korea, Greater China, India and Australasia. From 1982-2002, David held a number of strategic positions with AT&T and its related companies - where he played a key role in supporting and managing several global ventures. David was head of business sales and managed services for AT&T Asia Pacific. He also served as Regional Head of Concert Asia Pacific, a joint venture between BT and AT&T, where he led the global accounts sales, carrier services, and distribution organizations.   David was a founding officer of WorldPartners Company, a global telecommunications services venture between AT&T, KDD (Japan), Singapore Telecom and Unisource, serving as the Vice President, Marketing.   David holds a Master of Business Administration (Honors) with focus on Finance and Operations Research from the University of California, at Berkeley, Haas School of Business, and is also a Bachelor of Arts graduate in Economics with Engineering emphasis from the University.
        

          Pranesh Babu K,
          Chief Technology Officer
Pranesh took over as Chief Technology Officer in June 2010. He joined Sify Technologies in Oct 2000 and has worked in various capacities in the Technology division. Prior to this he was Senior Vice President – Network and Service Engineering, responsible for strategizing the Core Network and Access network and for developing Services.   He has been a key contributor to the Sify’s Network expansion and in developing Services for both the Enterprise and Consumer divisions.   Pranesh has over 21 years of experience in IT/ITES/ Telecom industry and has handled diverse responsibilities which include Projects, Service Delivery & Engineering. He started his Career with HCL Ltd, moving on to work with Hutchison Max Telecom as Chief Network Engineer and finally, Reliance Telecom Ltd as Project Manager, before joining Sify Technologies in 2000.   Pranesh holds an Engineering degree from university of Mysore in Electronics and Communications.

        

          Natesh Mani ,
          President – Sales and Marketing
-
        

          CR rao ,
          Chief Operating Officer
CR Rao was elevated in April 2013 as Chief Operating Officer.    He had joined us on 2nd March 2009 as Vice President - Strategy and was  responsible for the Administrative and HR functions in Sify. He has over 16 years of aviation industry experience and brings with him rich expertise in Strategic planning, operational management and organizational development initiatives. He has extensively worked on Business development and implementation of strategies and processes that drive enhanced business results and improve organisational capabilities.    He practiced law from 1987-1989. This was followed by assignments with Delta Tubes Pvt ltd and an impressive stint with Bobba Aviation Services – GSA Lufthansa Cargo, where he held various senior positions.    CR Rao holds graduate Degrees in Law and Commerce from Andhra University and postgraduate degree in Business Administration from Osmania University.

        





